enumValues.name: BACKGROUND_VIDEOS
enumValues.description: A list of videos to be used as the background for title/sponsor slides.

enumValues.name: CLOWDR_APP_VERSION
enumValues.description: A string representing the app version. Changing this causes the user's browsers to refresh.

enumValues.name: DISABLE_ALL_EVENTS_FOR_ITEM
enumValues.description: Boolean. Disable the "All times for this content" section of the Item pages.

enumValues.name: DISABLE_NEARBY_EVENTS
enumValues.description: Boolean. Disable the "Events around this content" section of the Item pages.

enumValues.name: ENABLE_BACKSTAGE_STREAM_PREVIEW
enumValues.description: Boolean. Whether to enable the backstage stream preview or not.

enumValues.name: ENABLE_EXTERNAL_RTMP_BROADCAST
enumValues.description: Boolean. Whether to enable the External RTMP Broadcast feature.

enumValues.name: FRONTEND_HOST
enumValues.description: A string representing the full frontend host URL for the conference. If not provided, this defaults to the system configuration.

enumValues.name: HIDDEN_EXHIBITIONS_LABEL
enumValues.description: String. Name for hidden exhibitions. Default: "Exhibition"

enumValues.name: INPUT_LOSS_SLATE
enumValues.description: An image to be displayed if AWS MediaLive loses input.

enumValues.name: MY_BACKSTAGES_NOTICE
enumValues.description: Additional text for the My Backstages modal.

enumValues.name: REGISTRATION_URL
enumValues.description: A string representing a valid URL for users to register for the conference.

enumValues.name: SCHEDULE_VIEW_VERSION
enumValues.description: Select different versions of the schedule view.

enumValues.name: SPONSORS_LABEL
enumValues.description: String. Label for the "sponsors" in the sidebar for when a conference uses a different term.

enumValues.name: SUPPORT_ADDRESS
enumValues.description: A string representing a valid email address for contacting the conference organisers.

enumValues.name: TECH_SUPPORT_ADDRESS
enumValues.description: A string representing a valid email address for contacting the service hosting company for technical support related to the conference.

enumValues.name: THEME_COMPONENT_COLORS
enumValues.description: JSON representation of a custom Component Map colors object.

enumValues.name: UPLOAD_AGREEMENT
enumValues.description: Text of the upload agreement or a URL to one.

enumValues.name: UPLOAD_CUTOFF_TIMESTAMP
enumValues.description: The time in milliseconds since the UNIX epoch, as a string.

enumValues.name: VISIBLE_EXHIBITIONS_LABEL
enumValues.description: String. Name for visible exhibitions. Default: "Exhibition"

enumValues.name: VONAGE_MAX_SIMULTANEOUS_SCREEN_SHARES
enumValues.description: Integer. The maximum number of simultaneous screen shares allowed in Vonage video chats.

enumValues.name: ACTIVE_SOCIAL_ROOMS
enumValues.description: Show a summary of the currently active social and discussion rooms

enumValues.name: AUDIO_FILE
enumValues.description: File for an audio clip (stored by Clowdr).

enumValues.name: AUDIO_LINK
enumValues.description: Link to an audio clip (audio is not embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: AUDIO_URL
enumValues.description: URL for an audio clip (audio is embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: CONTENT_GROUP_LIST
enumValues.description: List of content groups in the system.

enumValues.name: EXPLORE_PROGRAM_BUTTON
enumValues.description: Button that opens the explore program modal. Intended for use on the landing page.

enumValues.name: EXPLORE_SCHEDULE_BUTTON
enumValues.description: Button that opens the explore program modal with the Schedule tab open. Intended for use on the landing page.

enumValues.name: IMAGE_FILE
enumValues.description: File for an image (stored by Clowdr).

enumValues.name: IMAGE_URL
enumValues.description: URL to an image (embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: LINK_BUTTON
enumValues.description: A URL for a link button.

enumValues.name: LIVE_PROGRAM_ROOMS
enumValues.description: Show a summary of the currently live program rooms

enumValues.name: PAPER_FILE
enumValues.description: File for a paper (stored by Clowdr).

enumValues.name: PAPER_LINK
enumValues.description: Link for a paper (preview is not embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: PAPER_URL
enumValues.description: URL to a paper (preview may be embedded in Clowdr UI e.g. PDF JS viewer).

enumValues.name: POSTER_FILE
enumValues.description: File for a poster image (stored by Clowdr).

enumValues.name: POSTER_URL
enumValues.description: URL to a poster image (embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: SPONSOR_BOOTHS
enumValues.description: Show a summary of the sponsor booths

enumValues.name: VIDEO_COUNTDOWN
enumValues.description: Video file for counting down to a transition in a broadcast.

enumValues.name: VIDEO_FILE
enumValues.description: File for a video (stored by Clowdr).

enumValues.name: VIDEO_FILLER
enumValues.description: Video file for filler loop between events/during breaks in a broadcast.

enumValues.name: VIDEO_LINK
enumValues.description: Link to a video (video is not embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: VIDEO_PREPUBLISH
enumValues.description: Video file to be published in advance of the conference.

enumValues.name: VIDEO_SPONSORS_FILLER
enumValues.description: Video file for sponsors filler loop between events/during breaks in a broadcast.

enumValues.name: VIDEO_TITLES
enumValues.description: Video file for titles introducing an event during a broadcast.

enumValues.name: VIDEO_URL
enumValues.description: URL for a video (video is embedded in Clowdr UI).

enumValues.name: WHOLE_SCHEDULE
enumValues.description: Schedule view for the whole conference.

enumValues.name: ALLOW_EMAILS_TO_DOMAINS
enumValues.description: Allow-list (JSON array) of wildcard-match domains that the system should allow email to be sent to. See also NPM wildcard-match package.

enumValues.name: COOKIE_POLICY_LATEST_REVISION_TIMESTAMP
enumValues.description: The time of the latest revision of the host cookie policy. The value should be a Number representing the milliseconds elapsed since the UNIX epoch.

enumValues.name: COOKIE_POLICY_URL
enumValues.description: The URL to the host cookie policy. Note: If self hosting Clowdr, this must be your organisation's cookie policy - you cannot legally reuse, rely on or copy Clowdr's cookie policy.

enumValues.name: DEFAULT_FRONTEND_HOST
enumValues.description: A string representing the full frontend host URL for the app.

enumValues.name: DEFAULT_VIDEO_ROOM_BACKEND
enumValues.description: Default backend platform for video rooms

enumValues.name: EMAIL_TEMPLATES
enumValues.description: Templates for emails sent by the application.

enumValues.name: HOST_ORGANISATION_NAME
enumValues.description: The name of the organisation legally responsible for hosting this instance of the Clowdr software.

enumValues.name: PRIVACY_POLICY_LATEST_REVISION_TIMESTAMP
enumValues.description: The time of the latest revision of the host Privacy Policy. The value should be a Number representing the milliseconds elapsed since the UNIX epoch.

enumValues.name: PRIVACY_POLICY_URL
enumValues.description: URL to the host Privacy Policy. Note: If self hosting Clowdr, this must be your organisation's privacy policy - you cannot legally reuse, rely on or copy Clowdr's privacy policy.

enumValues.name: SENDGRID_API_KEY
enumValues.description: SendGrid API Key required for sending emails such as invites and submission requests

enumValues.name: SENDGRID_SENDER_NAME
enumValues.description: The name emails are from when sent via SendGrid.

enumValues.name: STOP_EMAILS_CONTACT_EMAIL_ADDRESS
enumValues.description: Contact address for people to request emails never be sent to them again.

enumValues.name: TERMS_LATEST_REVISION_TIMESTAMP
enumValues.description: The time of the latest revision of the host T&Cs. The value should be a Number representing the milliseconds elapsed since the UNIX epoch.

enumValues.name: TERMS_URL
enumValues.description: URL to the host T&Cs. Note: If self hosting Clowdr, this must be your organisation's terms - you cannot legally reuse, rely on or copy Clowdr's terms.

enumValues.name: VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY
enumValues.description: VAPID keys are used for push notifications and are generated automatically by the realtime service on first use.

enumValues.name: VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY
enumValues.description: VAPID keys are used for push notifications and are generated automatically by the realtime service on first use.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByUrl`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

enumValues.name: QUERY
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a query operation.

enumValues.name: MUTATION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a mutation operation.

enumValues.name: SUBSCRIPTION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a subscription operation.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment definition.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_SPREAD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment spread.

enumValues.name: INLINE_FRAGMENT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an inline fragment.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a variable definition.

enumValues.name: SCHEMA
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a schema definition.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a scalar definition.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an object type definition.

enumValues.name: FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field definition.

enumValues.name: ARGUMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an argument definition.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an interface definition.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a union definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM_VALUE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum value definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object type definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object field definition.

directives.name: cached
directives.description: whether this query should be cached (Hasura Cloud only)

args.name: ttl
args.description: measured in seconds

args.name: refresh
args.description: refresh the cache entry

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

args.name: if
args.description: Included when true.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.

args.name: if
args.description: Skipped when true.

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

args.name: reason
args.description: Explains why this element was deprecated, usually also including a suggestion for how to access supported similar data. Formatted using the Markdown syntax, as specified by [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/).

directives.name: specifiedBy
directives.description: Exposes a URL that specifies the behaviour of this scalar.

args.name: url
args.description: The URL that specifies the behaviour of this scalar.
